GameLogicState

public GameLogicState()
Create a GameLogicState. By default, GameLogicState is associated to a player application.

Method Detail

hasConnectionExited

public boolean hasConnectionExited()
Tells whether GameLogicState connection has exited or not. If channelsManager is not null, also tells if its channels have been closed.

Returns:
true if GameLogicState has exited.

connectionExit

public void connectionExit()
Set the GameLogicState to the connectionExited state. If channelsManager is not null, closes its channels.
